The paper deals with unsupervised speech representation learning using siamese networks, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SD (Sound), which deals with speech and audio processing. The paper also involves the use of siamese networks, which is a popular deep learning architecture used in computer vision and natural language processing. This makes cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. The paper also discusses the impact of sampling strategies on the performance of the network, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves the use of unsupervised learning, which is a common theme in cs.SD and cs.CL.
